This paper proposes a policy improvement algorithm for reinforcement learning that takes into account evaluation errors of the Q-function. The paper discusses the algorithm's performance in two tasks in the Atari Learning Environment, which suggests that it falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
